<subSubSection id="C368652E935E8E03F2AAFAA3FD7FFA58" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935E8E03F2AAFAA3FD7FFA58" blockId="7.[151,1437,1329,1859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">
The 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935E8E03F2F0FAA3FEE5FA80" box="[205,308,1329,1355]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">lectotype</typeStatus>
(present designation; recognized, but not published by B. Kataev) is a male, labelled: “Goudot? Barbaria”, blue card “Goudot”, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F030FAC7FCAAFAA4" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[525,891,1365,1391]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goudotii">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F030FAC7FD0DFAA4" box="[525,732,1365,1391]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Harpalus goudotii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F0D9FAC7FCAAFAA4" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[740,891,1365,1391]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. por J. Serrano”, “Lectoype” and “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F772FAC4FE65FA58" authority="Dejean" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sulphuripes" subSpecies="goudotii">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F772FAC4FE8CFA58" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">H. sulphuripes goudotii</emphasis>
Dejean
</taxonomicName>
det. B. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F031FAEBFD71FA58" author="Kataev, B. M." box="[524,672,1401,1427]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="721 - 736" refId="ref11345" refString="Kataev, B. M. (2002) Taxonomic, faunistic and nomenclatural notes on certain Palaearctic and Oriental Harpalini (Coleoptera, Carabidae). Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 34, 721 - 736." type="journal article" year="2002">Kataev 2002</bibRefCitation>
”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935E8E03F2FAFA0FFF0EF888" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935E8E03F2FAFA0FFC04F930" blockId="7.[151,1437,1329,1859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F2FAFA0FFEBDFA7C" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[199,364,1437,1463]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean (1829)</bibRefCitation>
studied four beetles as stated in the description: 
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F191FA0CFECBFA34" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">
Je possède quatre individus mâles de cette espèce: deux ont été rapportés de 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935E8E03F01FFA50FDA1FA10" box="[546,624,1474,1499]" name="Morocco" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Tanger</collectingCountry>
par M. Goudot; le troisième a été pris dans le département des Basses – Alpes...
</emphasis>
This taxon is considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F0CAFA77FB42FA34" authority="Germar, 1824" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1824" box="[759,1171,1509,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulphuripes">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F0CAFA77FC3DFA34" box="[759,1004,1509,1535]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Harpalus sulphuripes</emphasis>
Germar, 1824
</taxonomicName>
, mostly on the basis of having red-coloured femora (instead of darkened) and the geographic disjunction: the nominal subspecies inhabits Central and Mediterranean Europe whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F0B9F9BCFC5DF98C" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[644,908,1581,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sulphuripes" subSpecies="goudotii">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F0B9F9BCFC5DF98C" box="[644,908,1581,1607]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">H. sulphuripes goudotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the Maghreb, Andalusia and Sardegna (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F2A2F9C3FE7FF9A0" author="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W." box="[159,430,1617,1643]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="1810" refId="ref11718" refString="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (2017 c) Subtribe Harpalina Bonelli, 1810. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 515 - 562." type="book chapter" year="2017">Kataev &amp; Wrase, 2017c</bibRefCitation>
). The mention of Dejean of a beetle of this subspecies inhabiting the 
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F690F9C0FAECF9A0" box="[1197,1341,1617,1643]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Basses Alpes</emphasis>
is likely erroneous on geographic grounds, and also when considering the fact that mutations on femur colour may occur (ab. 
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F2F5F90BFE80F978" box="[200,337,1689,1715]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">lucidipennis</emphasis>
Schauberger, 1934). The aedeagus of the 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935E8E03F11FF90BFC58F978" box="[802,905,1689,1715]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">lectotype</typeStatus>
matches that illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F685F90BFAB2F97F" author="Antoine, M." box="[1208,1379,1689,1716]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine (1959)</bibRefCitation>
(that illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F30FF92FFE1EF91C" author="Jeannel, R." box="[306,463,1725,1751]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel, 1942</bibRefCitation>
, page 676 was erroneous according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F1BCF92FFBF4F913" author="Antoine, M." box="[897,1061,1725,1752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine, 1959</bibRefCitation>
: page 406). I could not find other beetles of this subspecies in Dejean’s collection to compare more aedeagi.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935E8E03F2FAF897FF0EF888" blockId="7.[151,1437,1329,1859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">
Different authors have dealt with this species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F0CEF897FC5EF8D4" author="Fuente de la, J. M." box="[755,911,1797,1823]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" refId="ref10490" refString="Fuente de la, J. M. (1927) Tablas analiticas para la clasificacion de los coleopteros de la Peninsula Iberica. Adephaga: I Cicindelidae, II Carabidae. J. Bosch, Barcelona, 415 pp." type="book" year="1927">Fuente, 1927</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F1A2F897FB91F8EB" author="Antoine, M." box="[927,1088,1797,1824]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine 1959</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F66CF897FB22F8D4" author="Jeannel, R." box="[1105,1267,1797,1823]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel, 1942</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F739F897FA49F8D4" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[1284,1432,1797,1823]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="344 - 386" refId="ref12516" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2004) Harpalina. In: Freude, H., Harde, K. W., Lohse, G. A. &amp; Klausnitzer, B. (Eds.), Die Kafer Mitteleuropas. Bd. 2 Adephaga 1: Carabidae (Laufkafer). Spektrum-Verlag, Heidelberg / Berlin, pp. 344 - 386." type="book chapter" year="2004">Wrase, 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F2AAF8BBFF02F888" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[151,211,1833,1859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" refId="ref12634" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2011) Genus Tschitscherinellus. Arndt, E., Schnitter, P., Sfenthourakis, S. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (Eds.), Ground beetles (Carabidae) of Greece. Pensoft, Sofia, pp. 163." type="book" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
